- "location_type" refers to the type of location, such as Urban or Rural;
- "premium_amount" is the amount of the insurance premium;
- "total_premium" is the sum of all premium amounts for each location type.

sql:
SELECT policy_id
FROM policies
WHERE premium_amount > (SELECT AVG(premium_amount) FROM policies);

SELECT AVG(p.premium_amount) AS average_premium_amount
FROM policies p
WHERE p.earthquake_coverage = 1;

